JOHANNESBURG &#8211; Members of South Africa&#8217;s ruling African National Congress will oppose a motion of no confidence against President Jacob Zuma in parliament set for April 18, the party said on Thursday.&#8220;We will abide by the decision of the ANC National Working Committee as announced by ANC secretary-general comrade Gwede Mantashe that the ANC does not and will not support this motion,&#8221; said a statement from ANC&#8217;s parliamentary chief whip. 